  <discussion>Draba arabisans is often confused with D. glabella (2n = 80); it is easily distinguished by having sessile (versus short-stalked) stellate trichomes on abaxial leaf blade surfaces and longer styles (0.2–)0.4–1 [versus 0.1–0.2(–0.4)] mm. Both species have twisted and plane fruits; D. arabisans has mostly twisted fruits; D. glabella has predominantly plane fruits. The complete absence of simple trichomes proximally on stems of D. arabisans can be a useful feature separating it from D. glabella, which often has at least some simple trichomes on the proximal half of the stem.</discussion>
  <discussion>Draba arabis Persoon is an illegitimate name, sometimes found in synonymy with D. arabisans.</discussion>
